{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01RdDLMUSYze3wVqFGVuBEKx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Full 3-node membership restored.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** The `rabbitmq-cookie-perpod` secret carried a drifted Erlang cookie for node-2 — its key was `driftedcookie` instead of `supersecretcookie` (the value used by node-0 and node-1). The StatefulSet's `copy-cookie` init container copies each pod's per-pod cookie from this secret, so after maintenance node-2 booted with a mismatched cookie, failed Erlang distribution auth against the cluster, and silently formed its own standalone single-node cluster.\n\n**Fix (native K8s resources only — no CRD/operator):**\n1. Patched the secret so `rabbitmq-2` = `supersecretcookie`.\n2. Deleted pod `rabbitmq-2` so the init container re-copied the corrected cookie (verified cookie now matches).\n3. Joined node-2 back: `stop_app` → `reset` → `join_cluster rabbit@rabbitmq-0…` → `start_app`.\n\n**Result:** All three nodes are now in the same cluster and running:\n- `rabbit@rabbitmq-0`, `rabbit@rabbitmq-1`, `rabbit@rabbitmq-2` all listed as Running Nodes\n- No data loss — the authoritative cluster data lives on nodes 0/1; only node-2's empty standalone state was reset before joining\n- No alarms, no network partitions; node-2 reports fully booted and running."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":548,"cache_read_input_tokens":41433,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":548},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7c3fb1ed-c7a8-43dd-bcee-f6d2171965e1","uuid":"e0a21b64-bb12-4e25-a8fe-5a7035c9d911","request_id":"req_011CcAY7KzXNy9HmZJHMNtT1"}
